tolua
------------------------------------------
tolua is a tool that greatly simplifies the integration of C/C++ code 
with Lua. Based on a cleaned header file, tolua automatically generates 
the binding code to access C/C++ features from Lua. Using Lua API and 
tag method facilities, tolua maps C/C++ constants, external variables, 
functions, classes, and methods to Lua.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-7
  lua-5.1.3-1

Build requirements:
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.8-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.tecgraf.puc-rio.br/~celes/tolua/

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.tecgraf.puc-rio.br/pub/users/celes/tolua/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack tolua-5.1b-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./tolua-5.1b-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/tolua-5.1b-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/tolua-5.1b-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/tolua.exe
  /usr/include/tolua.h
  /usr/lib/libtolua.a
  /usr/share/doc/tolua-5.1b/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/tolua-5.1b/README

------------------

